Wow it looks like you just randomly chose a wire to put the switch on. NONONO Switches always go on the HOT wire (The one that comes from the smaller plug).  Smack him one, Calli.

If you do this at home, keep in mind there is a 'hot" wire and "neutral" wire. TKOR connected the wires to the switch opposite of how they should be connected. You should break the hot and solder the neutral. The neutral side of the SPT style lamp cord has lines on it and feels rough when you run your finger across the jacket.  The hot side of the wire has a smooth jacket. And, yes, I realize it doesn't really matter in this instance, but if you follow the correct practice each time, you'll do it correctly when it really matters, like on a lamp socket where there is a higher chance of touching the metal neutral where the bulb screws in...
